      "role": "user",
      "content": "I see. It sounds like you're saying there are some clear-cut biological predispositions there. If that's the case, would it be considered bad coaching or even inefficient to try and force a client into a training style that goes against their \"natural\" biological strengths? Like, if I have a Black client, should I basically assume they're better off with explosive training rather than wasting time on heavy endurance work? Or does the science suggest they'll just hit a ceiling faster regardless of the programming?",
